In [2]:
def convert_to_geojson(data):
    
    features_list = []
    for reg in data.iterrows():
        my_poly = Polygon([[(reg[1].west,  reg[1].north),
                            (reg[1].west,  reg[1].south),
                            (reg[1].east,  reg[1].south),
                            (reg[1].east,  reg[1].north),
                            (reg[1].west,  reg[1].north)]])

        my_feature = Feature(geometry=my_poly)
        my_feature.id = int(reg[1].region)
        features_list.append(my_feature)
    feature_collection = FeatureCollection(features_list)
    return feature_collection

In [7]:
map_hooray = folium.Map(location=[40.748817, -73.985428],
                    zoom_start = 11) # Uses lat then lon. The bigger the zoom number, the closer in you get
folium.Marker([40.748817, -73.985428], popup='Empire State Building').add_to(map_hooray)
folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=convert_to_geojson(regions),
    name='Income Tax Per Capita',
    data=reg_stat1,
    columns=['reg_id', 'num_trips'],
    fill_color='YlGn',
    key_on='feature.id',
    fill_opacity=0.6,
    line_opacity=0.2,
    legend_name='    2016',
    highlight=True
).add_to(map_hooray)

In [10]:
map_hooray = folium.Map(location=[40.748817, -73.985428],
                    zoom_start = 11) # Uses lat then lon. The bigger the zoom number, the closer in you get
folium.Marker([40.689247, -74.044502], popup='Statue of Liberty').add_to(map_hooray)
folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=convert_to_geojson(regions),
    name='Income Tax Per Capita',
    data=reg_stat2[reg_stat2.num_trips >= 5],
    columns=['reg_id', 'num_trips'],
    fill_color='YlGn',
    key_on='feature.id',
    fill_opacity=0.6,
    line_opacity=0.2,
    nan_fill_opacity=0.1,
    legend_name='       2016',
    highlight=True
).add_to(map_hooray)

map_hooray
